# commands to run the backend and frontend on both macOS and Windows

ðŸ“¦ Backend (Django)

    âœ… 1. Setup Virtual Environment
    
    Only if env/ folder doesn't exist --
    
    For -- macOS / Linux:
            
            >> python3 -m venv env
            >> source env/bin/activate
    
    For -- Windows (Command Prompt):
    
            >> python -m venv env
            >> env\Scripts\activate
    
    For -- Windows (PowerShell):
    
            >> python -m venv env
            >> .\env\Scripts\Activate.ps1
    
    
    âœ… 2. Install Dependencies
        # Navigate to the backend folder
            >> cd backend 
    
        #Then install Python packages:
            >> pip install -r requirement.txt
            >> pip install pymysql
    
    ðŸ” Note: The file is typically named requirements.txt â€” if yours is requirement.txt, ensure it's consistent.
    
    âœ… 3. Run Django Development Server
    
            >> python manage.py runserver
    
    ðŸ” You can now access your backend 


ðŸŒ Frontend (React / Vite)

    âœ… 1. Install Dependencies
       # Navigate to the frontend directory:
            >> cd frontend
            >> npm install
    âœ… 2. Run the Dev Server
            >> npm run dev

    ðŸ” This starts the frontend server 


ðŸ› ï¸ Tools & Technologies Used
    
